{
  "texts": [
    "This enables a combinatorial coding system that supports a wide range of odor perception.",
    "Artificial intelligence, especially the combination of molecular docking and machine learning, has been applied to predict odorant-receptor interactions.",
    "These approaches support high-throughput screening of molecular pairs and help identify novel scent compounds.",
    "They also improve understanding of how olfactory signals are encoded at the molecular level.",
    "The olfactory pathways encompass several key structures, including the olfactory bulb, where the initial processing of olfactory information occurs (Shipley et al. 2008)."
  ]
}